Sam_Details

Search elements: carbon including methane

a suite of three instruments: 
				mass spectrometer 
				- seperate elements and compounds by mass identification
				
				gas chromatograph
				- heat soil and rock samples until they vaporize
				- separate the resulting gases into various components for analysis
				
				tunable laser spectrometer
				- measure the abundance of various isotopes of carbon, hydrogen, and 				  oxygen in atmospheric gases such as methane, water vapor, and carbon				  dioxide

accuracy : 10 parts per thousand

other elements: hydrogen, oxygen, nitrogen
